FBIS3-37635 "drsov035_t_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia Agreement Close on Paldiski Naval Base LD1902163994 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1500 GMT 19 Feb 94 LD1902163994 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] Estonia and Russia are close to concluding an agreement on dismantling the nuclear training center at the former Soviet naval base in the town of Paldiski near Tallinn. [passage omitted] During the talks, Russian Vice Admiral Viktor Ovchinnikov confirmed readiness to allow IAEA [International Atomic Energy Agency] specialists into the center, however, only after the removal of the nuclear rods and secret equipment.
